The paper deals with competitive algorithms for combinatorial optimization problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of submodular and subadditive functions also suggests a connection to these areas.
